column5: went to cooks this morning, was dieing to try out some lures i read about and was tempted to buy. switched around alot, starting from swedish pimple, jiggig raps, lil foxees, but the rig of the day was bottom bouncer rig with dead/alive minows. lots of smalls, but managed to land some decent 12"s. couple managed to get away. was in 30 fow.
Sweet! I'm gonna get me some of those in the next couple days!!!! I haven't eaten perch since last ice, last season!!!!  Sinker
Nice looking perch there...especially the 2 big ones strategically arranged on the top of the pile
Theres a nice big fat one that stands out in that pile of perch!! Congrats on that one!
Now I'm really getting the itch. Thanks for the report.
How thick was the ice where you were. I'm wanting to get out, but there has to be at least six inches of ice before I venture out on tto the ice. Scooter
Cook's Bay from the Pumphouse/Old Homestead Rd south is all about 8".  With about 5" of snow on top.  Rick
....Attaboy.    You know all these perch reports are starting to affect me palate.
WTG, beauty load of Perch you got there, especially the big ones on the top!
